[31m-## 7. Background incoming call behavior[m
[31m-[m
[31m-### Telnyx recommended flow[m
[31m-[m
[31m-```[m
[31m-Socket connected (foreground) → INVITE on WebSocket → answer in app[m
[31m-App background/killed → socket closes → Telnyx sends FCM/APNs VoIP push[m
[31m-User taps Accept → setPushMetaData(isAnswer:true) → handlePushNotification()[m
[31m-→ socket reconnects → INVITE arrives → accept (or auto-accept if early accept)[m
[31m-```[m
[31m-[m
[31m-**Critical Telnyx guidance (Flutter docs — “Handling Background Calls”):**[m
[31m-[m
[31m-- When app is **backgrounded**, socket may stay open but OS won't surface INVITE → **manually disconnect** when entering background so Telnyx sends push.[m
[31m-- Use lifecycle listener (e.g. `flutter_fgbg`) — background: `disconnect()`, foreground: reconnect unless returning from push accept path.[m
[31m-- Use `FGBGEvents.ignoreWhile` when showing CallKit UI to avoid disconnect during full-screen incoming UI.[m
[31m-- Late push: if `message.sentTime` > ~60s, treat as missed call.[m
[31m-[m
[31m-### Current implementation[m
[31m-[m
[31m-| Scenario | Actual behavior |[m
[31m-|----------|-----------------|[m
[31m-| Foreground, socket ready | INVITE via WebSocket; in-app + optional native UI | ✅ Telnyx-aligned |[m
[31m-| Foreground, socket not ready | FCM → CallKit + in-app state | ✅ |[m
[31m-| App killed | FCM/PushKit → CallKit → boot → `handlePushNotification` | ✅ |[m
[31m-| App **backgrounded**, socket still connected | **Keeps WebSocket + 2min presence heartbeat** | ❌ **Opposite of Telnyx recommendation** |[m
[31m-| Background disconnect on lifecycle | ❌ `AppLifecycleBridge` only handles **resumed** |[m
[31m-| Late notification timeout | ❌ Not implemented |[m
[31m-| Push accept before INVITE | ✅ `_waitingForInvite` |[m
[31m-| SDK 10s INVITE timeout after push accept | ✅ Automatic in SDK 4.2.0 |[m
[31m-[m
[31m-### Gaps[m
[31m-[m
[31m-1. **No background socket disconnect** — largest behavioral deviation from Telnyx Flutter guidance. User may miss calls when app is backgrounded but not killed (no push, INVITE not surfaced).[m
[31m-2. **No late-push stale detection** (60s rule).[m
[31m-3. **Debug terminated push** — Telnyx warns this always fails in debug; must not be used to sign off production readiness.[m
[31m-[m
[31m-### Production impact[m
[31m-[m
[31m-- **High:** “App in recent apps but not visible” is a common user state — **missed inbound calls** without push or notification.[m
[31m-- **Medium:** Stale pushes may show phantom incoming UI.[m
[31m-[m
[31m-### Required fixes[m
[31m-[m
[31m-| Priority | Fix |[m
